itively, literally or figuratively (not necessarily with the idea of return to the starting point); generally to retreat; often adverbial, again"},{"code":"H7725","text":"return","lemma":"שׁוּב","translit":"","pos":"adverb","disp":1,"lit":"build","med":"build","tho":"circumcise","range":"to turn back (hence, away) transitively or intransitively, literally or figuratively (not necessarily with the idea of return to the starting point); generally to retreat; often adverbial, again"},{"code":"H7759","text":"O Shulamite","lemma":"שׁוּלַמִּית","translit":"","pos":"article","disp":0,"lit":"Shulamite","med":"Shulamite","tho":"Shulamite","range":"peaceful (with the article always prefixed, making it a pet name); the Shulammith, an epithet of Solomon's queen"},{"code":"H7759","text":"in the Shulamite","lemma":"שׁוּלַמִּית","translit":"","pos":"article","disp":0,"lit":"Shulamite","med":"Shulamite","tho":"Shulamite","range":"peaceful (with the article always prefixed, making it a pet name); the Shulammith, an epithet of Solomon's queen"}],"div":[{"code":"H2372","lemma":"חָזָה","lit":"behold","tho":"look"},{"code":"H4264","lemma":"מַחֲנֶה","lit":"army","tho":"band"},{"code":"H7725","lemma":"שׁוּב","lit":"build","tho":"circumcise"}],"struct":"contains a main verb"},"12":{"tokens":[{"code":"H3045","text":"Or ever I was aware","lemma":"יָדַע","translit":"","pos":"verb","disp":2,"lit":"know","med":"know","tho":"know intimately","range":"to know (properly, to ascertain by seeing); used in a great variety of senses, figuratively, literally, euphemistically and inferentially (including observation, care, recognition; and causatively, in"},{"code":"H4818","text":"me like the chariots","lemma":"מֶרְכָּבָה","translit":"","pos":"noun","disp":0,"lit":"chariot. See also H1024 (בֵּית הַמַּרְכָּבוֹת)","med":"chariot. See also H1024 (בֵּית הַמַּרְכָּבוֹת)","tho":"chariot. See also H1024 (בֵּית הַמַּרְכָּבוֹת)","range":"a chariot"},{"code":"H5315","text":"my soul","lemma":"נֶפֶשׁ","translit":"","pos":"adverb","disp":3,"lit":"soul","med":"soul","tho":"life/self","range":"properly, a breathing creature, i.e. animal of (abstractly) vitality; used very widely in a literal, accommodated or figurative sense (bodily or mental)"},{"code":"H5993","text":"of Amminadib","lemma":"עַמִּי נָדִיב","translit":"","pos":"noun","disp":0,"lit":"Amminadib","med":"Amminadib","tho":"Amminadib","range":"Ammi-Nadib, probably an Israelite"},{"code":"H7760","text":"made","lemma":"שׂוּם","translit":"","pos":"verb","disp":0,"lit":"appoint","med":"appoint","tho":"bring","range":"to put (used in a great variety of applications, literal, figurative, inferentially, and elliptically)"}],"flags":[{"code":"H3045","lemma":"יָדַע","disp":2,"note":"Dispute level 2: multiple significant translation options."},{"code":"H5315","lemma":"נֶפֶשׁ","disp":3,"note":"נֶפֶשׁ — \"soul\" (Greek-influenced: non-material self) vs. \"life\" (the whole living person) vs. \"self\" (the person as subject). Hebrew nefesh is embodied, not a separate immaterial substance."}],"div":[{"code":"H3045","lemma":"יָדַע","lit":"know","tho":"know intimately"},{"code":"H5315","lemma":"נֶפֶשׁ","lit":"soul","tho":"life/self"},{"code":"H7760","lemma":"שׂוּם","lit":"appoint","tho":"bring"}],"struct":"contains a main verb; ⚑ theologically contested vocabulary"},"8":{"tokens":[{"code":"H4436","text":"queens","lemma":"מַלְכָּה","translit":"","pos":"noun","disp":0,"lit":"queen","med":"queen","tho":"queen","range":"a queen"},{"code":"H4557","text":"without number","lemma":"מִסְפָּר","translit":"","pos":"noun","disp":0,"lit":"account","med":"account","tho":"tale","range":"a number, definite (arithmetical) or indefinite (large, innumerable; small, a few); also (abstractly) narration"},{"code":"H5959","text":"and virgins","lemma":"עַלְמָה","translit":"","pos":"noun","disp":0,"lit":"damsel","med":"damsel","tho":"maid","range":"a lass (as veiled or private)"},{"code":"H6370","text":"concubines","lemma":"פִּילֶגֶשׁ","translit":"","pos":"no